I tried this code: https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=nightly&mode=debug&edition=2021&gist=b6fe50e5acdd6b8c1e5f4d3603b60c0a

```rust
#![feature(nll)]

struct DB;
impl DB {
    fn contains(&self, _: &str) -> bool {
        true
    }
    fn resolve(&self, _: &str) -> Result<&'static str, String> {
        Ok("".into())
    }
}

fn f() -> (DB, &'static str) {
    let locked_rev = Some("abc");
    let mut maybe_db = Some(DB);
    if let (Some(rev), Some(db)) = (locked_rev, maybe_db) {
        if db.contains(rev) {
            return (db, rev);
        }
        maybe_db = Some(db);
    }
    if let (None, Some(db)) = (locked_rev, maybe_db) {
        if let Ok(rev) = db.resolve("abc") {
            return (db, rev);
        }
        maybe_db = Some(db);
    }
    (maybe_db.unwrap(), "")
}
```

I expected to see this happen: The code compiles successfully.

Instead, this happened: The code gives an error:

```
error[E0382]: use of moved value: `maybe_db`
  --> src/lib.rs:24:44
   |
15 |     let mut maybe_db = Some(DB);
   |         ------------ move occurs because `maybe_db` has type `Option<DB>`, which does not implement the `Copy` trait
16 |     if let (Some(rev), Some(db)) = (locked_rev, maybe_db) {
   |                                                 -------- value moved here
...
22 |         maybe_db = Some(db);
   |         ------------------- this reinitialization might get skipped
23 |     }
24 |     if let (None, Some(db)) = (locked_rev, maybe_db) {
   |                                            ^^^^^^^^ value used here after move
```

This error is incorrect; there is no case where `maybe_db` is moved and also control flow can reach line 24 without first reaching line 22. If the `if let` block isn't entered, `maybe_db` isn't moved.

### Meta

`rustc --version --verbose`:
```
1.60.0-nightly (2022-01-12 1bd4fdc943513e1004f4)
```
